    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03251.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">5 East 63<hi rend="underline">d</hi> Street, New York City</name>
                    <date when="1891-12-01" rend="right">12/1/'91.<ptr target="loc.03251_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt Whitman:—</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Your book,<ptr target="loc.04811_n6"/> which is in every way most satisfactory, arrived this morning.</p>
			<p>Thank you for your promptness, and your kind confidence in sending it before receiving the balance.</p>
			<p>I remit with this the $3.40 lacking, and will be grateful if you will notify me of its safe receipt.</p>
			<p>Wishing you renewed health and years of life to enjoy it—</p>
			<closer>
                <signed rend="right">J. Wm. Lloyd.</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
				<p>Will induce others to purchase your book if I can.</p>
			</postscript>
            <note type="editorial" resp="#unk" place="left">J Wm Lloyd</note>
